Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 tablespoon milk in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in half of the whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 2 cups cold milk into large bowl. Add dry pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.) Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Just before serving, garnish with remaining whipped topping and 2 tablespoons shaved chocolate. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.